rComments: The class 1502 was rather easy, most answers for the tests could be found in the notes. Though attendance is graded, I don't think I actually listened to any of his lectures because he is very monotone and his lectures can get boring. Tests were reasonable and easy with a bit of studying.

Lots of readings for this class. Appreciated the structure of modules and predictability of this course as an English student in a French course. Found the exam and midterm were more than fair. Sought to include current events in the course.

This was a good teacher for the most part. He was helpful in answering questions, he had a good amount of quizzes to boost your grade. His class helped me expand my knowledge, even through an online class. However, he can be a little boring at times reading his PowerPoint but this material itself is good.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Lots of homework', 'Participation matters']

rComments: Cours ennuyant mais vraiment pas sévère quand il note.
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', 'Get ready to read', 'Gives good feedback']

rComments: Good teacher won't deny it but the lectures are far too long and have too much information. Tough grader and too many group projects.

Other than rushing through his powerpoint because he presents too much content, Prof Martel is great. His content is interesting and the assignments closely reflect what was learned in class. He gives readings but all of the assignments were class content heavy, which was also great.

I struggled with the hefty lectures and work. This was a class that requires dedication and attention all the time. Martel is so monotone and speaks so fast that I caught myself daydreaming during his lectures. I stopped attending class halfway through the semester and crammed the exam and got an A. So if you can avoid this class then do try to!
5 questions développement où il désire 1 page de réponse pour chaque question de l'examen final, et en plus 10 QCM où nous sommes chronometrés 15 minutes pour les faire. Inadmissible.

Il a beaucoup d'expérience et il connait très bien son contenu. Malgré la qualité de son contenu, le cours est désordonné et la matière n'est pas toujours dans le bon ordre. Préparez-vous à lire beaucoup de textes, ils vous permettent de mieux comprendre des sujets en particulier, mais si vous ne les lisez pas tous, vous pourrez répondre à l'examen
Prof gentil, les examens sont justes si tu étudies bien. Il fait son possible pour rendre le cours intéressant. Les assistants sont très gentils. Toutefois, il y a énormément de lectures.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Gives good feedback', 'Lecture heavy']

rComments: Prof gentil mais très monotone. Énormément de lectures.
I hated this class, I was so lost the entire time. The prof is so monotone and talks way too fast. Not a fan.

Un bon professeur qui a très bien organisé son cours pour l'apprentissage en ligne. Les présentations sont parfois monotones. Cours assez chargé pour la première année, mais les évaluations ne sont pas difficiles. Les attentes du professeur sont raisonnables. Les TA sont efficaces et aident les élèves à réussir.
Great professor u ve to love the course first and everything will fit on step at the time.

The teacher is very knowledgeable, but very monotone and boring. He gives SO MANY lectures and asks very very specific questions about them in the exams. If you can avoid taking a class with him, I recommend you to do so.
Very nice teacher, interesting classes and fair exams. Attendance is mandatory and make sure to participate!
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Get ready to read', 'Lecture heavy']

rComments: Professor Martel is one of the most genuine profs that you can have at uOttawa. Any political science or public administration student that goes through their undergrad without taking a class from him is missing out on his extensive knowledge of the public service and his kindness towards his students.

Terrible teacher. Had him for one of my classes and there WAY too many lectures!! Plus he has you do these mandatory discussion groups and you absolutely need to participate if you want to get a good grade. No thank you, next pls.
Do not recommend.

I had this prof for two of my classes and it was the worst classes I have ever taken. Here throws a bundle of information at you will reading every PowerPoint word by word. Very monotone. Watch out for the group project. Oh, and he gives no exam guideline. He gives you a review of about 70 pages (Slides).
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Participation matters', 'So many papers']

rComments: Monsieur Martel est un homme gentil et dévoué, il est quelque fois difficile à suivre par contre. Pour le travail de groupe, choisissez bien votre groupe. Les TA sont bien mais manque un peu de maturité. En général cest un cours avec beaucoup de matière et quelque fois décousu en enseignant la matière. Bonne chance

Vraiment mauvais. Le monsieur est gentil, mais très ennuyant. Il ne va pas en profondeur dans la matière. C'est inutile d'aller au cours, mais vous devez faire les lectures pour bien réussir! Attention, travail de groupe, mais vous pouvez choisir votre équipe.

je n'ai pas été aux cours et j'ai fini avec un A. faut s'assurer de maitriser les powerpoints, faire une vite lecture des points importants du manuel de cours (manuel neuf est 120$). 3 DGD, 1 examen mi-ssession, 1 projet de groupe, 1 examen non cumulatif. semble comme beaucoup d'info mais c'est simple... pas besoin d'aller aux cours....
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Accessible outside class', 'Group projects']

rComments: Please, for your own good, do not take a class with him. His lectures are SO SO boring and his exams are just mad. He asks you questions about the readings (and he gives you A LOT of them), but they are just so specific that its nearly impossible to answer them properly. Also, GROUP PROJECT. Got stuck with 2 lazy students and it was hell.
run while u still have a choice
teacherRatingTags: ['So many papers', 'Tough grader', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: If you love yourself, do not take a class with prof Martel. He seems like a good man and loves what he does, but his lectures are so monotone and extremely hard to get through without taking a nap. On the plus side, he's an extremely easy marker and he posts everything on blackboard so you don't have to pass and can probably get a good grade.

Très monotone. Le cours en tant que tel n'est pas super difficile, mais il y a beaucoup de lectures (qui n'ajoutent vraiment rien au cours). Ses examens sont super difficiles (ex: il donne une citation et demande c'est qui l'auteur), mais si tu vas au cours c'est pas trop pire.

Le prof n'est pas pire, mais ses cours ne sont pas stimulants. Il a plusieurs lectures à faire (en ligne), mais elles sont très importantes pour l'examen. Les choix multiples peuvent être difficiles, mais les questions à développement ne sont pas. Des groupes de discussion et des travaux aident votre note. Cours quand même pas trop difficile.
This prof made it very difficult for anyone to become interested in what he was teaching... please avoid!

Great professor. Very knowledgeable. I had him twice and if you're putting the efforts, he'll help you succeed. Yes, his lectures are monotone but the guy's a total deadpan which makes his classes very funny. Definitely one of my favorite prof at UOttawa.

For me, he was a bad teacher. I took him for my politics class and I'm dropping out of his class so I can take it again next year with a different prof. He 's terribly boring, and super duper tough grader. Avoid if possible!!!!

Professor Martel genuinely cares about his students and their success. His lectures are boring but the majority of exam content is covered in them. Il y a aussi beaucoup de TRs so if you don't like them, I would avoid this prof. I would strongly recommend this prof for FI students, he is leniant on French mistakes and speaking in DGDs.

This professor could be good if he didnt make his 3 hour lectures seem longer than they are. He never let the class leave earlier than 9:40pm and only gave us 5-10 minute breaks at the half-way point. He was always well prepared for his lectures but failed to engage the class or focus on the topics that were really important.
C'est un bon prof, un peu réservé et pas très loquace, mais il sait quand meme rendre son cours intéressant.
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Get ready to read', 'Gives good feedback']

rComments: Un des meilleures profs avec un parcours formidable qui lui permet de mieux expliquer  la matière. Pour ce qui concerne les lectures, tout dépend des cours, pleins de lecture et travaux de groupe pour le PAP2720 par exemple, sinon un grand respect!!
Le cours le plus long tu vas jamais prendre. Très monotone et je suis 100% il ne souris jamais. Avoid at all costs.
Très bon prof mais il y'avait une tonne de lecture à faire pour le cours. il est juste dans sa correction et rend la matière très intéressante.
Had him twice, good teacher overall. His lectures are quite boring, but just go to classes and you'll do well. Easy marker but beware of multiple long group projects.

Please pay attention to the other comments. I ignored them and took this class and regretted it greatly. Attendance is crucial and important to your grade. Amount of reading is ridiculous, and there is a multiple choice exam on specific quotesauthors from the readings. Unless you are good at memorizing details avoid!
He''s so boring it''s hard to stay focused. Ok class overall.

Avoid at all costs! His lectures are unbelievably boring, and his entire teaching methodology is quantity over quality, forcing you to read hundreds of pages a week and never saying anything relevant. I often skip just so I can do the readings, but he also checks attendance every few classes so it's like playing Russian roulette with your GPA.

AVOID! Super hard grader, wants specific answers from slides or readings. Class average was 49% on midterm. The readings are way to long upwards of 100 pages a week (textbook and links) and thats on top of his countless slides filled with dates and other useless info. Also very boring to top it all off.

Frustrating professor: bad at explaining (would use broad unhelpful example, or define word using the word he's trying to define), MC quizzes (using his own wording which greatly differs from the text), but an easy essay exam generously marked. Avoid is possible, otherwise, learn the slides and understand them by using the textbook (not the class).
Funny guy, mediocre professor. Multiple choice questions are tricky. He's a really nice guy, but his teaching is very boring; I'd avoid the class if you could.
You need to go to class. He give's exam with things we never seen!
No need to go to class, just reed and understand his powerpoints. Got an A that way, sure anybody could do so. Not very interesting teacher in class, but will help if you go to his office hours.
Great Prof! Easy to understand, and makes early mornings bearable. Interesting topics if you enjoy ethics! If you take the time to see him about a question, he is really helpful and explains clearly.

I CANT GET ENOUGH OF THIS MAN, LIKE I HONESTLY COULDNT HAVE GOTTEN THROUGH FIRST YEAR WITHOUT HIS HELP.  :D very interesting prof and very knowledgeable, knows what he is talking about. cant wait to take more classes with him:)... go to his office if you need any help, he is always there waiting to help;) ;)

THIS GUY IS THE BEST PROFESSOR EVER!!! Hands down made first year the best year ever... I can't believe there are people this amazing in this world :)) Thank you Mr. Martel! you are such a great guy.. Cute too ;)

His lecture slides are absolutely brutal to study off, but if you study them you will do well on the quizes/midterms. He's a great guy, but you can't blame him for such a boring class, seriously social context of business... What do you expect?
Don't take any of his classes! Extremely boring and not helpful and not very good at explaining. No need to go to class.
This guy is soo useless as a teacher, he doesn't know how to teach at all. He provides no guidance for exams but exams are not that difficult.

This guy is as boring as it gets, it's hard to not fall asleep. Probably the worst prof in first year. Not only that, but he isn't helpful in the slightest bit. If you want to enjoy your first year at Telfer, avoid him. It's as simple as that.
Don't even consider going to class just read the Power Points , this guy is so boring i feel like slapping myself for even taking his class.

He is extremely boring and monotone. He looks at me in a strange way, what a weirdo. I went to his office hours and he didn't help me. I still passed no thanks to him. Good luck, you guys will need it.
